Minister of Youth and Sports Development Mr. Sunday Dare at the weekend organised a table tennis competition to honour the late Soun of Ogbomoso, Oba Jimoh Oyewumi. He said the maiden DAD Foundation Table Tennis Competition was part of activities lined up for the 40 days Fidau in honour of the monarch. The minister said the competition would promote peace and engage youths to make them productive and maximise their talents. Dare urged them not to limit themselves, but be committed, saying there was great opportunity in sports.   2023: ‘Zoning good, but competence better’     Council to go after debtors     Media firm unveils Lagos Show Podcast   Former Director of Kwara State Sports Council Mr. Tunde Kazeem described the minister as a performer, whose accessibility and humility were unparalleled. - Advertisement - President of Ogbomoso Community Youth Forum Rev. Peter Olaleye hailed Dare for not only initiating the competition, but also investing in building a befitting sports centre in the town. A representative of the minister’s friends, Dr. Dan Okeke, an All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftain in Abia State, said they were in Ogbomoso to support Dare because he was always there for “us despite his hectic schedule.” Cash gifts were presented to winners of the competition.